history.content:
An email will go out to the list of students who received the email you quote (sent to our majors who were on the waitlist for 16B in late December or early January) who did not make it into the class sometime this afternoon. Since the instructors will be using 999L section for lab enrollments (something that was not decided until a few days ago), there won't be a need to get feedback about lab preferences so, as possible, students from that list will be enrolled directly into the class -- hopefully today but by Tuesday at the latest.

One important thing to note is that this will count as phase 1 units towards the 13.5 unit phase 1 budget for each student. Anyone who decides to drop to make room for another phase one course will not be given any priority at all in the future. That means it will be risky and should only be done if taking that course is more important to an individual student than being able to graduate in LSCS and/or EECS.

children.subject: No. If you made a decision to repurpose those units early, the department will not move you into the class manually. You should definitely use phase 1 units and stay on the waitlist (if you aren't able to enroll directly into the class).

If I was waitlisted for 16B for this semester but dropped from the waitlist really early (was at ~position 400), will there be a similar policy or should we just phase 1 and hope for the best on the waitlist? I will be a junior next semester

history.content:
<md>In near beginning this semester, I've received an email from EE department, saying that 

"*If you are not able to be enrolled for spring 2021, you will be the first students to be enrolled in Fall 2021 (per a commitment from the dept chairs -- note this priority will not exist in spring 2022 or later). I will keep this list and send email or a google form out to students in that situation once the schedule is finalized and before phase 1 begins so that you can communicate your lab preferences, etc., and then I will enroll you into the class assuming you are registered for the term.*"

Phase 1 is coming next week, but I have not received any email about that yet. Is there any update?</md>
